<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="reward-n">reward <strong><em>n</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /rɪ'wɔːd/    美 /rɪ'wɔːrd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-c-u">1.★ <strong>[C] &amp; [U] 报答；报酬；奖赏</strong></h4>
<p>sth that you are given because you have done sth good, worked hard, etc.：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>My grandmother says that a good deed is its own reward. 
我祖母说善举本身就是回报。</p><footer>2012 浙江改</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>This job is difficult, but the <strong>financial rewards</strong> are great. 
这项工作很辛苦，但报酬丰厚。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The school has a system of rewards and punishments to encourage good behaviour. 
学校有奖惩制度来鼓励良好的行为。</p></div>

<h4 id="2-c">2.★ <strong>[C] 悬赏金；赏金：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>There is a <strong>reward for</strong> information leading to catching the killer. 
为抓捕凶手提供消息的人有悬赏金。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The old lady is offering a <strong>reward of</strong> $50 to anyone who finds her cat for her! 
不管谁找到她的猫，老太太都会给50美元的赏金！</p><footer>北师大⑤ – 14</footer></div>

<h3 id="reward-award-prize">辨析 reward, award, prize</h3>
<p><strong>reward ** 一指因工作、贡献等而得到的“回报”、“报酬”。二指因给警方提供帮助或帮助他人找回失物而得到的“赏金”。
</strong>award ** 指因某种突出的成就而由官方颁发的奖赏或荣誉，可以是“奖 (品)”、“奖状”、“奖金”等。
**prize ** 指因在某方面作出巨大的贡献或在竞赛、比赛中胜出而获得的“奖赏”、“奖品”。</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>the <strong>Nobel Prize for</strong> Physics / Medicine / Peace 
诺贝尔物理学奖/医学奖/和平奖</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She won the <strong>first prize</strong> at the speech contest. 
她在演讲比赛中获得了一等奖。</p></div></div>